# Cursor AI Rules for Hy-lee Shopify

## Project Structure

This is a **dual-stack** project:

- `theme/` — Shopify Liquid theme (CSS + Liquid templating)
- `hydrogen/` — Hydrogen/Remix storefront (React + TypeScript + Tailwind v4)

Determine which stack you're working in by the file path. Rules differ per stack.

## Context Files

Before making changes, read the relevant context:

- **Always**: `guidelines/AGENT_EDITING_INSTRUCTIONS.md`
- **Theme work**: `docs/COMPONENT_INVENTORY.md`, `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`
- **Hydrogen work**: `hydrogen/CLAUDE.md`, `hydrogen/design-references/<component>/figma-spec.md`

---

## Theme Rules (`theme/`)

### Component-First Development

- ALWAYS check `theme/snippets/` before creating any UI element
- If a component exists, USE IT. If not, CREATE IT FIRST as a reusable snippet
- All UI components MUST be in `theme/snippets/` as `.liquid` files
- Component styles MUST be in `theme/assets/component-{name}.css`

### Design Tokens

ALWAYS use CSS custom properties from `theme-variables.css`:

```css
/* Correct */
color: var(--color-primary);
padding: var(--spacing-md);

/* Wrong */
color: #4a90a4;
padding: 16px;
```

### File Naming

- Components: `{name}.liquid`
- Component CSS: `component-{name}.css`
- Section CSS: `section-{name}.css`
- Template CSS: `template-{name}.css`

### CSS Naming (BEM)

```css
.component-name {}
.component-name__element {}
.component-name--modifier {}
```

---

## Hydrogen Rules (`hydrogen/`)

### Stack

- **Framework**: Shopify Hydrogen + React Router 7
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with `@theme` tokens in `app/styles/app.css`
- **Components**: CVA variants + `cn()` merger (`app/lib/utils.ts`)
- **Icons**: Lucide React icons
- **Testing**: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (e2e + visual)

### Design Tokens

Use Tailwind classes mapped from `app/styles/app.css` `@theme` block:

```
--color-primary (#2ac864) → *-primary
--color-secondary (#2699a6) → *-secondary
--color-text-muted (#666) → *-text-muted
```

Never hardcode hex colors. Use token-mapped Tailwind classes.

### Figma Design Reference

When building/refining UI, follow the mandatory process in `hydrogen/CLAUDE.md`:

1. Capture reference via Figma MCP tools
2. Save to `hydrogen/design-references/<component>/`
3. Build against the spec with pixel-accurate measurements
4. Visual comparison via Playwright screenshots

---

## Shared Rules (Both Stacks)

### Branching

Format: `<type>/<scope>/<short-description>`
Types: `feature`, `bugfix`, `hotfix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`

### Commits

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
Example: `feat(sections): add hero banner section`

### Pre-Commit (MANDATORY)

Run ALL checks before every commit. Zero exceptions.

**Theme changes:**
```bash
pnpm format && pnpm format:check && pnpm theme-check && pnpm test && pnpm validate
```

**Hydrogen changes:**
```bash
pnpm format && pnpm format:check && pnpm typecheck && pnpm build && pnpm test
```

### Pattern Capture (workflow-agent)

After fixing bugs or completing features, capture reusable patterns:

```bash
workflow verify --fix --learn    # Auto-capture fix patterns
workflow learn:record            # Manual pattern recording
workflow learn:list              # View captured patterns
workflow sync --push             # Share with registry
```

### Self-Improvement

When you discover workflow issues or improvements:

1. Document in `.workflow/improvements/YYYY-MM-DD-<id>.md`
2. Categorize: validation | scopes | documentation | performance | security | ux
3. Submit: `workflow suggest "<description>"`

### Implementation Plans

For changes touching 3+ files, create a plan in `plans/<FEATURE_NAME>_PLAN.md` BEFORE coding. Update checkboxes as work progresses.

### DO NOT

- Hardcode colors, spacing, or design values in either stack
- Use inline styles
- Skip pre-commit checks
- Commit without running validation
- Add new dependencies without checking `guidelines/LIBRARY_INVENTORY.md`
- Create components without checking for existing ones first
- Skip pattern capture after meaningful fixes

### Commands

```bash
# Theme
pnpm theme:dev          # Start theme dev server
pnpm theme-check        # Shopify theme linter
pnpm theme:push         # Deploy to Shopify

# Hydrogen
pnpm hydrogen:dev       # Start Hydrogen dev server
pnpm hydrogen:build     # Production build
pnpm hydrogen:typecheck # Type-check

# Shared
pnpm format             # Format all code
pnpm test               # Run unit tests
pnpm test:e2e           # Run E2E tests
pnpm validate           # Full validation

# Workflow
pnpm workflow            # Run workflow agent
pnpm verify              # Verify changes
pnpm verify:fix          # Auto-fix issues
```
